OL,3,CEngland fans expecting comfortable win
OL,4,Cas flights booked for knockouts
OL,6,FBradley Littlechild, 30, who now lives
OL,7,Fin Edinburgh, told PA: "So we've
OL,8,Fbooked hotels where you can do the
OL,9,Fcancellation for Toronto and Atlanta.
OL,11,F"We haven't booked our flights yet, so
OL,12,Fas soon as the game finishes, we need
OL,13,Fto book flights or a bus or something,
OL,14,Fbecause I think the flights have gone
OL,15,Fup.
OL,26,@oD@XOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782638299
OL,3,CEngland fans expecting comfortable win
OL,4,Cas flights booked for knockouts
OL,6,F"It's something like 350 dollars so
OL,7,Fit's just going to sting us. And we've
OL,8,Fobviously got to pay for the hotel and
OL,9,Fthen we've got to go back to New York
OL,10,Fto fly back to London ` so it's a
OL,11,Fjourney.
OL,13,F"We're here because we follow England
OL,14,Fhome and away. It's just money at the
OL,15,Fend of the day ` I don't think you can
OL,16,Fput a price on watching England at the
OL,17,FWorld Cup."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUyD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782638299
OL,3,CEngland fans expecting comfortable win
OL,4,Cas flights booked for knockouts
OL,6,FHe added: "It's England and it's
OL,7,Ffootball ` we're all betting men and I
OL,8,Fthink we would like to say that
OL,9,FEngland are going to go through, but
OL,10,Ffor the sake of spending 500-600
OL,11,Fdollars, that'd be a very sore one if
OL,12,Fyou have to then pay money to go to
OL,13,FToronto."
OL,15,FGiving his thoughts on England's
OL,16,Fchances against Panama, Mr Littlechild
OL,17,Fsaid: "Arrogantly, we should beat them
OL,18,F` but someone asked.... what was my
OL,19,Fprediction for the Ghana game and I
OL,20,Fsaid 4-0.
OL,26,@nD@KOUuD@IO]yD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1782638299
OL,3,CEngland fans expecting comfortable win
OL,4,Cas flights booked for knockouts
OL,6,F"But I think tomorrow we should beat
OL,7,Fthem, I'd like to say 2 to 3-0."
OL,9,FSupporters have also said transport to
OL,10,Fthe game in New Jersey from New York
OL,11,Fhas also been expensive.
OL,13,FMr Slaughter told PA: "We're on the
OL,14,Ftrain to the ground tomorrow, so I
OL,15,Fthink that was ` well they reduced it,
OL,16,Fbut I think it was about 90 dollars or
OL,17,Fsomething like that.
OL,19,F"But we've got to get there somehow."
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@`O]uD@WOU{D@AOU{D@eO]
